          <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">🔵 AI Blue: Systematic Color Recognition Bias in Vision-Language Models</p>
          <p style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--text-label); margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">We tested 4 VLMs × 40 colors × 480 observations. Commercial models miss intermediate hues. 95% of AI-generated UI colors land on blue-purple. First quantitative link between VLM color bias and the "AI Slop" phenomenon.</p>
          <div style="font-size: 0.75rem; display: flex; gap: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap;">
            <a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19159702">📄 Paper (DOI)</a>
            <a href="https://github.com/kenimo49/ai-blue-color-bias">💻 Code & Data</a>
            <span style="color: var(--text-muted);">March 2026 · Zenodo</span>
